01:03:27,440 --> 01:03:29,795
- Is trying to pick up on my boyfriend...
- Stop it. Stop it.

954
01:03:29,840 --> 01:03:32,070
- In front of my face.
- Why don't you just lay off of her?

955
01:03:32,160 --> 01:03:34,116
- Your sister's losing her mind.
- Do you think I look invisible?

956
01:03:34,160 --> 01:03:36,276
I am not losing my mind!

957
01:03:36,360 --> 01:03:39,636
I am not losing my mind!
I am just tired, Jordan.

958
01:03:39,720 --> 01:03:42,632
- I am tired. I am tired.
- Ellen, let's go.

959
01:03:42,720 --> 01:03:44,597
Being my mother is very tiring.

960
01:03:44,680 --> 01:03:46,910
Oh, come on. There's nobody more
different than your mother than you.

961
01:03:46,960 --> 01:03:49,428
- Come on. Let's go.
- That is the stupidest thing that you have ever said.

962
01:03:49,520 --> 01:03:51,795
- Okay. Great.
- That's the stupidest thing you've ever said.

963
01:04:08,840 --> 01:04:10,671
Oh, God.

964
01:04:12,000 --> 01:04:15,913
- Ellie.
- Yeah.

965
01:04:17,840 --> 01:04:22,118
- You all right?
- Yeah, I just have a headache.

966
01:04:22,160 --> 01:04:25,072
- What happened to Jordan? I heard Brian go upstairs...
- Yeah, yeah.

967
01:04:25,160 --> 01:04:28,072
He has to go to work tomorrow,
so he just took the train back.

968
01:04:28,160 --> 01:04:30,754
Hmm. You sure you're all right?

969
01:04:30,800 --> 01:04:33,360
How do you do this...

970
01:04:33,440 --> 01:04:36,432
every day, all day in this house...

971
01:04:36,520 --> 01:04:39,876
and no one notices?

972
01:04:39,920 --> 01:04:41,831
Doesn't that drive you crazy?

973
01:04:44,080 --> 01:04:47,390
But this is my family, Ellie.

974
01:04:47,440 --> 01:04:49,795
These are the people I love.

975
01:04:51,920 --> 01:04:55,071
Maybe it's time for you to start
thinking about going back to New York.

976
01:04:55,120 --> 01:04:57,953
Maybe you should go back
to the city...

977
01:04:58,000 --> 01:05:02,516
to your work and your writing and
all those things that you like to do.

978
01:05:02,600 --> 01:05:06,798
That's what's important, sweetie.

979
01:05:09,680 --> 01:05:12,069
You know, we can get somebody
to help out around here. That's not...

980
01:05:15,840 --> 01:05:20,038
But you did a great job tonight.
You should be proud of yourself.

981
01:05:20,080 --> 01:05:21,957
Night-night, sweetheart.

982
01:05:25,040 --> 01:05:27,600
Good night.

983
01:05:49,680 --> 01:05:51,671
Hello.

984
01:05:51,760 --> 01:05:53,671
Mr. Tweedy, hi.

985
01:05:53,760 --> 01:05:57,036
A press conference? Where?

986
01:05:58,560 --> 01:06:01,757
The next train
is not till 5:00. Shit.

987
01:06:01,840 --> 01:06:03,796
- Then Casey...
- No, don't send Casey. I'll be there.

988
01:06:16,240 --> 01:06:18,117
- Excuse me.
- Yeah.

989
01:06:27,280 --> 01:06:30,113
Excuse me. No.
I'm sorry. Excuse me.

990
01:06:30,160 --> 01:06:32,390
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

991
01:06:53,600 --> 01:06:55,556
Too late is unacceptable.
You said you'd get the story.

992
01:06:55,600 --> 01:06:57,511
And I will.
I'll find him.

993
01:06:57,560 --> 01:06:59,755
Look, I've got a contact at Sullivan's
office. He's getting on a plane at 9:00.

994
01:06:59,840 --> 01:07:02,274
No, no, no. I've worked
on this thing for three months.

995
01:07:02,320 --> 01:07:04,834
- He's staying at the Plaza Athene. I can check it out.
- Anyone can figure that out.

996
01:07:04,880 --> 01:07:07,758
No, I will meet him there. I'll meet
him at the Plaza Athene before he leaves.

997
01:07:07,840 --> 01:07:09,876
This is my story,
goddamn it!

998
01:07:09,960 --> 01:07:12,155
This is my story.

999
01:07:23,080 --> 01:07:25,799
Good night, sir.

1000
01:07:40,160 --> 01:07:42,469
Taxi!

1001
01:07:50,240 --> 01:07:53,357
Hey, don't I know you?

1002
01:07:53,440 --> 01:07:56,113
- I don't think so.
- Yes, we went to Harvard together.

1003
01:07:56,200 --> 01:07:58,350
Ellen Gulden.
You were a couple of years ahead of me.

1004
01:07:58,440 --> 01:08:02,956
I wrote for the women's magazine,
Peeved Eves.

1005
01:08:03,000 --> 01:08:07,073
I remember Peeved Eves.

1006
01:08:07,120 --> 01:08:10,635
- Well, it's nice to see you.
- Yeah, yeah. Nice to see you too.

1007
01:08:10,720 --> 01:08:14,190
Got to get to J.F. K in time
for the last commuter shuttle.

1008
01:08:14,280 --> 01:08:17,272
It's my daughter's
birthday today.

1009
01:08:17,360 --> 01:08:20,511
If you're going to J.F. K,
I can give you a lift.

1010
01:08:22,800 --> 01:08:26,270
I moved to Seattle a couple of months
ago to get away from all the cameras...

1011
01:08:26,320 --> 01:08:29,835
my ex-wife and my ex-kids.

1012
01:08:29,920 --> 01:08:33,435
Yeah, you know, I think I saw something
about that on television.

1013
01:08:33,520 --> 01:08:37,274
- How horrible.
- You know what's strange?

1014
01:08:37,360 --> 01:08:39,669
- One minute you're in school and the
next minute you look up... - Mm-hmm.

1015
01:08:39,760 --> 01:08:41,591
And your life's all turned around
and screwed up.

1016
01:08:41,680 --> 01:08:46,151
- Yes, I know. Yeah.
- You try and you try to get ahead.

1017
01:08:46,240 --> 01:08:48,834
Somewhere in it all you just...

1018
01:08:48,880 --> 01:08:51,440
You lose yourself.

1019
01:08:51,520 --> 01:08:53,351
- And you never know when
it's gonna come. - Mm-hmm.

1020
01:08:53,440 --> 01:08:57,399
Comes out of nowhere.
Bang. It's just...

1021
01:08:57,480 --> 01:08:59,789
- Your life is a disaster.
- Yep.

1022
01:08:59,880 --> 01:09:01,871
Oh, I just hope I can make it up
to my wife and kids.

1023
01:09:01,960 --> 01:09:03,916
You know, that's all that counts.
That's all that counts.

1024
01:09:04,000 --> 01:09:05,831
Yeah, you're right.

1025
01:09:05,920 --> 01:09:10,152
They're the ones who love you.
That's what counts.

1026
01:09:18,440 --> 01:09:21,671
I'm reading, Mom.
And baby cows are calves.

1027
01:09:25,200 --> 01:09:27,794
You're right.

1028
01:09:48,640 --> 01:09:50,949
G.A. Tweedy here.
Leave a message after the noise.

1029
01:09:51,040 --> 01:09:54,112
Mr. Tweedy, it's Ellen.

1030
01:09:54,160 --> 01:09:56,037
Uh...

1031
01:09:57,800 --> 01:10:00,234
Listen, I waited
for Sullivan...

1032
01:10:00,280 --> 01:10:04,068
outside of his hotel,
and, uh...

1033
01:10:04,120 --> 01:10:07,749
Well, he never showed.

1034
01:10:11,920 --> 01:10:14,639
Damn.

1035
01:10:14,920 --> 01:10:17,832
Here we go.

1036
01:10:21,520 --> 01:10:26,116
They're several reasons why I asked you
here today, one of which...

1037
01:10:26,160 --> 01:10:28,594
- Hi, John. Peter.
- George.

1038
01:10:30,400 --> 01:10:34,154
One of which is to ask you...

1039
01:10:36,680 --> 01:10:39,274
why you were
so hostile with me...

1040
01:10:39,360 --> 01:10:41,191
at Thanksgiving.

1041
01:10:41,280 --> 01:10:45,592
I know this is not
the best situation for any of us.

1042
01:10:45,680 --> 01:10:49,673
But I'm trying, Ellen.
I'm trying to be patient.

1043
01:10:56,880 --> 01:11:01,192
I have some questions
that I'd like to discuss with you.

1044
01:11:01,280 --> 01:11:04,556
- I don't think I want to talk about the interview.
- I do.

1045
01:11:07,880 --> 01:11:09,711
Okay, Ellen.

1046
01:11:09,800 --> 01:11:13,509
How come Mom waited so long?

1047
01:11:13,600 --> 01:11:16,512
Why didn't she go
to the doctor sooner?

1048
01:11:16,560 --> 01:11:21,031
- What are you talking about?
- Was it because you didn't want your world disrupted?

1049
01:11:21,120 --> 01:11:24,908
Because you needed her
to keep your life running smoothly?

1050
01:11:25,000 --> 01:11:26,831
Like you need me now?

1051
01:11:26,920 --> 01:11:29,070
- What the hell are you doing?
- Because she can't do it all?

1052
01:11:29,160 --> 01:11:33,756
Well, do you have any idea
what it takes to keep your life...

1053
01:11:33,840 --> 01:11:36,479
- running so smoothly?
- Ellen, have you lost your mind?

1054
01:11:36,560 --> 01:11:39,836
- Maybe.
- Keep your voice down.

1055
01:11:39,920 --> 01:11:42,434
- This is inappropriate.
- It is appropriate!

1056
01:11:42,480 --> 01:11:46,393
Everything at our house has changed,
but you don't know about it.

1057
01:11:46,480 --> 01:11:49,916
Because you're behaving
as though life goes on as usual.

1058
01:11:50,000 --> 01:11:53,470
Well, life as we know it is done!
This is real life!

1059
01:11:53,520 --> 01:11:56,159
Fuck fiction!

1060
01:11:56,240 --> 01:11:58,071
Less is not more!

1061
01:12:00,600 --> 01:12:03,194
You have taken sabbaticals
for the great American novel.

1062
01:12:03,280 --> 01:12:05,111
Why not one for Mom?

1063
01:12:05,200 --> 01:12:08,875
Why won't you participate
in the most important thing...

1064
01:12:08,920 --> 01:12:11,434
that has happened in your life?

1065
01:12:11,520 --> 01:12:14,080
She needs you.

1066
01:12:15,400 --> 01:12:17,675
Why is it always more important
for you to hear...

1067
01:12:17,760 --> 01:12:20,558
what some writer has to say
than me?

1068
01:12:22,280 --> 01:12:24,271
And Brian?

1069
01:12:27,120 --> 01:12:29,236
Hey.

1070
01:12:34,480 --> 01:12:37,836
Hey, what other tricks do you use
besides your fucking apples...

1071
01:12:37,920 --> 01:12:41,595
to get your writing juices
flowing, Dad?

1072
01:12:41,680 --> 01:12:43,671
Cheating on Mom, is that one?

1073
01:12:43,760 --> 01:12:47,548
I will hire a full-time nurse.
You are going back to New York.

1074
01:12:47,600 --> 01:12:49,875
What other tricks?

1075
01:12:54,400 --> 01:12:57,153
Several people have mentioned...

1076
01:12:57,200 --> 01:13:00,829
a heated argument that you had
with your father...

1077
01:13:00,880 --> 01:13:03,997
outside the campus cafe.

1078
01:13:04,080 --> 01:13:08,358
It was shortly
after Thanksgiving.

1079
01:13:08,400 --> 01:13:10,277
Do you recall the incident?

1080
01:13:11,600 --> 01:13:15,149
Uh-huh.
Yeah, I remember.

1081
01:13:18,880 --> 01:13:23,078
It was a stressful time...

1082
01:13:23,120 --> 01:13:26,999
and there was a lot to do
and it was hard.

1083
01:13:27,080 --> 01:13:29,469
So, there was no problem
between you and your father?

1084
01:13:29,520 --> 01:13:31,954
No.

1085
01:13:32,040 --> 01:13:34,554
Or your father
and your mother?

1086
01:13:34,640 --> 01:13:37,677
My mother and my father?

1087
01:13:37,760 --> 01:13:40,911
Of course not.
It was a busy time.

1088
01:13:41,000 --> 01:13:43,673
I mean, I was
a full-fledged Minnie.

1089
01:13:43,760 --> 01:13:48,390
I remember we were making
the, uh, ornaments...

1090
01:13:48,480 --> 01:13:50,471
the craft ornaments
with the feathers and the sequins...

1091
01:13:50,560 --> 01:13:53,757
for my mother's
Christmas tree in the square.

1092
01:13:53,840 --> 01:13:56,229
And, uh, I would climb
up the ladder...

1093
01:13:56,320 --> 01:13:58,880
and she would tell me
where to put them.

1094
01:13:58,960 --> 01:14:01,190
So, it was fun.

1095
01:14:03,120 --> 01:14:04,951
It was a lot of fun.

1096
01:14:10,880 --> 01:14:13,838
Yeah, it's really not that bad.

1097
01:14:13,920 --> 01:14:15,831
Yeah, it's okay.

1098
01:14:15,920 --> 01:14:19,310
You know, I always used to try
to get you to go see Santa.

1099
01:14:19,400 --> 01:14:22,312
For years and years.
And then when you were 8 years old...

1100
01:14:22,400 --> 01:14:26,871
you got in line and you went to
the very front, pulled his beard off...

1101
01:14:26,960 --> 01:14:29,838
- Pulled his beard off.
- And yelled, "Fraud!"

1102
01:14:29,920 --> 01:14:33,913
Your dad was so proud of you.

1103
01:14:34,000 --> 01:14:36,195
Well, guess what?

1104
01:14:39,440 --> 01:14:43,319
- I'm getting in the line. Yes.
- Oh, now you want to.

1105
01:14:48,160 --> 01:14:51,675
- Uh-huh.
- Good girl. Go on. Be good.

1106
01:14:54,840 --> 01:14:58,276
- Ellen Gulden.
- Hello.

1107
01:14:58,320 --> 01:15:00,197
- Hi.
- I know what you want:

1108
01:15:00,240 --> 01:15:03,232
A new computer
and Diane Sawyer's job.

1109
01:15:03,280 --> 01:15:07,592
I'm here, okay?
Okay, here we go.

1110
01:15:11,600 --> 01:15:14,478
Nothing for me, Mayor.

1111
01:15:14,560 --> 01:15:18,633
Santa.

1112
01:15:18,680 --> 01:15:22,309
I guess maybe it is for me.

1113
01:15:23,760 --> 01:15:26,957
I really... l...

1114
01:15:31,400 --> 01:15:33,231
Mom!

1115
01:15:34,280 --> 01:15:36,669
Mom!

1116
01:15:36,720 --> 01:15:39,518
Excuse me, is there
a phone that I can use?

1117
01:15:39,600 --> 01:15:41,431
Sure.

1118
01:15:41,520 --> 01:15:43,750
This line right here.
Press nine to get out.

1119
01:15:47,800 --> 01:15:51,918
Answer the phone, Dad.

1120
01:16:41,760 --> 01:16:43,751
Ellen?

1121
01:16:47,760 --> 01:16:49,591
Mom's in the hospital.

1122
01:16:49,680 --> 01:16:54,959
The cancer has progressed
much more quickly than we had expected.

1123
01:16:55,040 --> 01:16:58,157
I'm sorry, but I think it's best
to stop the chemotherapy.

1124
01:17:03,680 --> 01:17:07,753
Uh, you know what? Um, I'm not
ready to stop the chemotherapy.

1125
01:17:07,840 --> 01:17:10,115
I'm afraid there's
no more we can do.

1126
01:17:10,160 --> 01:17:13,436
We all need now to focus...

1127
01:17:13,520 --> 01:17:15,875
on helping her through
this next part.

1128
01:17:15,920 --> 01:17:17,797
I'm putting her on morphine.

1129
01:17:17,840 --> 01:17:21,469
You'll need to give her
one tablet twice a day for the pain.

1130
01:17:21,520 --> 01:17:24,910
They shouldn't be chewed or crushed
because they might become toxic.

1131
01:17:26,800 --> 01:17:31,191
I am sorry.
I'll get you the prescription.

1132
01:17:45,760 --> 01:17:48,069
So, what do you think of the wheels?

1133
01:17:48,160 --> 01:17:50,355
Oh, they look wonderful.

1134
01:17:50,440 --> 01:17:52,715
- You like 'em?
- Oh, gosh, it's like what we used to do...

1135
01:17:52,800 --> 01:17:55,758
- to the bikes when you were kids.
- Uh-huh.

1136
01:17:55,840 --> 01:17:57,671
- You look beautiful.
- Oh, Brian.

1137
01:17:57,760 --> 01:17:59,591
You do.

1138
01:17:59,680 --> 01:18:02,274
- No coat?
- No, I don't need one. I'm layered, honey.

1139
